Fluorescence intensity variation of 1 towards the newly prepared PD isomer solution and their oxidized product was summarized. It was found that I/I0 is less than 0.9 in ethanol solution indicated that PPD had been oxidized (Fig. 10
                        ). For MPD, when using CCQDs-based fluorescent probe, I/I0 in ethanol solution was greater than that in 1.1 indicating that MPD had been completely oxidized. When using fluorescein-based fluorescent probe, I/I0 in ethanol solution was greater than 1.1 indicating that MPD had been completely oxidized. When using ratio fluorescent probe, I/I0 in ethanol solution was greater than 1.2 indicating that MPD had been completely oxidized. For OPD, I/I0 in ethanol solution was greater than 1.02 in CCQDs-based fluorescent probe can be regarded as had been oxidized, I/I0 in ethanol solution was greater than 1.0 in fluorescein-based fluorescent probe can be regarded as had been oxidized, I/I0 in ethanol solution was less than 1.15 in ratio fluorescent probe can be regarded as had been oxidized (Fig. 11
                        ).
